parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the seat belt cable attachment can cause the seat belt to become ineffective, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt cable attachment breaks off with no load
the seat belt fails to restrain the occupant
the seat belt opens with moderate forward pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to become ineffective, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: the rear seat belt buckle will not latch

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust manifold bolts can cause exhaust leaks, leading to hot fumes entering the vehicle cabin, which can be a safety hazard. Additionally, it can lead to costly repairs and potential damage to other engine components.
symptoms: Exhaust manifold bolts shear or fall off
hot fumes entering the vehicle cabin

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracking and leaking of the exhaust header can cause exhaust leaks, leading to hot fumes entering the vehicle cabin, which can be a safety hazard. Additionally, it can lead to costly repairs and potential damage to other engine components.
symptoms: hot fumes entering the vehicle cabin

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A broken or loose front suspension component can cause uneven tire wear, reduced vehicle stability, and compromised handling, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: clunking or rattling noises from the front suspension

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sudden Unintended Acceleration (SUA) with Stuck Throttle
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to lose control, resulting in accidents, injuries, and even fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
the throttle becomes stuck wide open
the vehicle goes into high speed in reverse
the vehicle is difficult to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering tie rod can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents or near-miss situations, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: unusual noises or vibrations while steering.
